topics.tweet_search_prompt:
Search X for the most popular/high-engagement posts about US unemployment, consumer spending pressure, and economic slowdown impacts.

Search queries to use (combine with since:{since_date}):
1. unemployment OR "jobless claims" OR "job cuts" layoffs since:{since_date}
2. "consumer spending" decline OR slowdown OR pressure since:{since_date}
3. "credit card delinquency" OR "consumer debt" stress OR default since:{since_date}
4. "restaurant closures" OR "same store sales" decline since:{since_date}
5. BNPL "buy now pay later" default OR delinquency since:{since_date}
6. "discretionary spending" OR "consumer confidence" drop OR plunge since:{since_date}
7. "travel demand" OR airline OR cruise slowdown OR bookings decline since:{since_date}

Focus on:
- US labor market deterioration signals (JOLTS, NFP, claims, WARN notices)
- Consumer credit stress (delinquencies, charge-offs, subprime defaults)
- Retail and restaurant traffic declines, same-store sales misses
- BNPL/consumer lending deterioration (Affirm, Klarna, SoFi)
- Travel and leisure demand softening (airlines, cruises, hotels, ride-share)
- Payment volume trends as leading indicators (Visa, Mastercard, PayPal)
- Federal/state government workforce reductions (DOGE layoffs)
- Wage growth deceleration and its impact on consumer behavior

Prioritize posts from: macro economists, consumer analysts, credit strategists, restaurant/retail analysts, labor market researchers, financial journalists
Exclude: political commentary without economic data, job posting promotions, generic recession fear without specific metrics

