topics.tweet_search_prompt:
Search queries (append since:{since_date} to each):

1. CPI OR "core CPI" OR "inflation rate" hotter OR sticky OR cooling since:{since_date}
2. PCE OR "core PCE" OR "personal consumption expenditures" above OR below OR surprise since:{since_date}
3. "fed funds rate" OR "interest rate" cut OR hike OR hold OR pause since:{since_date}
4. FOMC OR "dot plot" OR "fed minutes" hawkish OR dovish OR pivot since:{since_date}
5. Powell OR "fed chair" inflation OR rates OR "soft landing" OR stagflation since:{since_date}
6. "breakeven inflation" OR "inflation expectations" OR TIPS rising OR falling since:{since_date}
7. "shelter inflation" OR "owners equivalent rent" OR OER sticky OR declining since:{since_date}
8. "wage growth" OR "unit labor cost" OR "employment cost index" inflationary OR moderating since:{since_date}
9. tariff OR tariffs inflation OR prices impact OR "price increases" since:{since_date}
10. "real rates" OR "terminal rate" OR "neutral rate" OR r-star higher OR lower since:{since_date}

Focus on:
- CPI component breakdown (headline vs core, goods vs services, supercore, trimmed mean/median CPI)
- PCE trends (core PCE MoM/YoY, gap to Fed's 2% target, 3m/6m annualized run-rate)
- FOMC policy path (dot plot median, FF futures implied cuts/hikes, SEP projections)
- Inflation expectations (UMich/NY Fed surveys, 5y5y forward BEI, TIPS market moves)
- Shelter inflation (OER/rent index lag effects, divergence from real-time rent trackers like Zillow/Apartment List)
- Wage and labor costs (Atlanta Fed Wage Tracker, ECI, unit labor costs, wage-price spiral risk)
- Tariff and supply shocks (China/universal tariff CPI uplift estimates, import price index)
- Financial conditions (FCI, credit spreads, mortgage rates and housing market transmission)
- Global policy divergence (ECB/BOJ/BOE rate differentials, USD strength and imported inflation effects)

Prioritize posts from:
- Fed officials and former policymakers
- Wall Street chief economists
- Rates/bond strategists
- Inflation-focused analysts
- Fed-beat journalists (e.g. Nick Timiraos)
- BLS/BEA data visualization accounts

Exclude:
- Opinion posts without specific data points
- Politically-motivated Fed criticism lacking analysis
- Crypto/meme-stock context rate mentions
- Posts recycling outdated data releases
